cable serv 13   = [[Numericable]]<br><small>([[France]])</small>\n| cable chan 13   = Channel 246\n| cable serv 14   = [[UPC Polska]]<br><small>([[Poland]])</small>\n| cable chan 14   = Channel 778\n| cable serv 15   = [[Cablevision]]<br><small>([[Argentina]])</small>\n| cable chan 15   = Channel 680\n| cable serv 16   = [[Movistar TV]]<br />{{small|([[Peru]])}}\n| cable chan 16   = Channel 768\n| cable serv 17   = [[SkyCable]]/[[Destiny Cable]]<br><small>([[Philippines]])</small>\n| cable chan 17   = Channel 190\n| cable serv 18   = [[Cablelink]]<br><small>([[Philippines]])</small>\n| cable chan 18   = Channel 312\n| cable serv 19   = [[:zh-tw:\u51f1\u64d8\u516c\u53f8|Kbro]] ([[Taiwan]])\n| cable chan 19   = Channel 234 (SD)\n| cable serv 20   = [[Virgin Media]]<br><small>([[United Kingdom]])</small>\n| cable chan 20   = Channel 311\n| cable serv 21   = [[Serbia Broadband|SBB]]<br><small>([[Serbia]])</small>\n| cable chan 21   = Channel 180\n| cable serv 22   = [[NET TV]]<br><small>([[Brazil]])</small>\n| cable chan 22   = Channel 628\n| iptv serv 1     = [[Univision]]<br><small>([[Mongolia]])</small>\n| iptv chan 1     = Channel 410\n| iptv serv 2     = Tigo<br><small>([[Colombia]])</small>\n| iptv chan 2     = Channel 601\n| iptv serv 3     = [[CHT MOD]] ([[Taiwan]])\t\n| iptv chan 3     = Channel 153 (HD)\n| iptv serv 4     = [[Singtel TV]] ([[Singapore]])\n| iptv chan 4     = Channel 349 (HD)\n| iptv serv 5     = [[MEO (Portugal)]]<br><small>([[Portugal]])</small>\n| iptv chan 5     = Channel 147\n| iptv serv 6     = [[Tele2 Netherlands]]\n| iptv chan 6     = Channel 228\n| iptv serv 7     = [[T-Mobile Netherlands]]\n| iptv chan 7     = Channel 215\n| iptv serv 8     = [[Indonesia Digital HOME|Indihome]] ([[Indonesia]])\n| iptv chan 8     = Channel 450 ([[Standard-definition television|SD]])<br>Channel 948 ([[High-definition television|HD]])\n| online serv 1   = Yelo TV\n| online chan 1   = [http://yelotv.be/tv/mtv-live Watch live] (Belgium only)\n| online serv 2   = [[Ziggo#Ziggo_GO|Ziggo GO]] (Netherlands)\n| online chan 2   = [https://www.ziggogo.tv ZiggoGO.tv] (Europe only)\n}}\n\n'''MTV Live HD''' is an international 24-hour HD music [[pay television|pay television network]] that is operated by [[ViacomCBS Networks International]]' subsidiary [[ViacomCBS Networks EMEAA]].<ref>[http://www.mtv.pl/news/MTVNHD-Launches-On-Sky-Hd-2178049/ ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110524145328/http://www.mtv.pl/news/MTVNHD-Launches-On-Sky-Hd-2178049/ |date=May 24, 2011 }}</ref> The channel is available in [[Europe]], [[Latin America]], [[Oceania]], [[Middle East and North Africa]] and [[Asia]].\n\n==Overview==\nMTV Live HD, the first ever international high definition service dedicated to music, offers a mix of programming from [[MTV Europe|MTV]]. MTV Live HD is operated by MTVNI's Emerging Markets group, who produce and broadcast the channel from its [[Warsaw]] hub.<ref name=\"c21media01\">{{citation | title = MTVN Lat Am completes regional rejig | date = 2009-03-19 | publisher = C21 Media | url = http://www.c21media.net/news/detail.asp?area=1&article=48314}}</ref> The English-language service also features original and acquired shows, and programming from MTVNI's multi-branded library.\n\nThe channel's mix of programming includes shows produced by other international MTV production units in Southern Europe, the UK and Latin America.<ref name=\"c21media01\"/> From the beginning the channels' programming schedules were split into two blocks - MTV HD and Nickelodeon HD, but from October through December 2010 the channel only aired music related programs; it restarted airing Nickelodeon shows at the weekends but earlier in the morning. From July 1, 2011 the channel began to focus primarily on live music programming.\n\n===History===\nThe channel was launched on September 15, 2008 in some parts of [[Europe]] as MTVNHD ([[MTV Networks]]-[[high-definition television|High Definition]])<ref name=announcement>{{cite press release| publisher = [[MTV Networks International]]| date = 2008-09-01| title = MTV Networks International Launches First Ever Music and Kids International High Definition Service - MTVNHD| url = http://www.viacom.com/NEWS/Pages/newstext.aspx?RID=1192234| accessdate = 2010-10-14| url-status = dead| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110608032903/http://www.viacom.com/NEWS/Pages/newstext.aspx?RID=1192234| archivedate = 2011-06-08}}</ref> and in [[Latin America]] by the end of 2008.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSN2947062320080901 | work=Reuters | title=MTV Networks to launch international HD channel | date=1 September 2008}}</ref> The channel continued to launch in new countries throughout 2010, including Australia where it first became available in standard-definition.\n\nOn July 1, 2011, MTVNHD was rebranded as MTV Live HD, with a new logo to match the new logos of all other MTV channels revealed on the same date.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://brandingsource.blogspot.com/2011/06/new-logos-mtv-international.html|title=New logos: MTV international|publisher=The Branding Source|date=21 June 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20110701220600/http://brandingsource.blogspot.com/2011/06/new-logos-mtv-international.html|archivedate=1 July 2011}}</ref> However, in the UK and Ireland the channel remained as MTVNHD. In Australia MTVN Live was rebranded as MTV Live.\n\nOn April 23, 2012, MTVNHD was rebranded as MTV Live HD in the UK and Ireland, along with the launch of a standard-definition MTV Live.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadbandtvnews.com/2012/02/10/revamp-for-mtv-hd/|title=Revamp for MTV HD|publisher=Broadband TV News|date=10 February 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130225022947/http://www.broadbandtvnews.com/2012/02/10/revamp-for-mtv-hd/|archivedate=25 February 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn April 9, 2013, MTV Live HD ceased broadcasting in France after to the launch of the HD's versions of the French MTV channels.\n\nOn October 1, 2013, MTV Live HD and MTV Live revamped the channels logo as part of a global rebrand.\n\nOn November 3, 2013, MTV Live and MTV Live HD ceased broadcasting on Foxtel's service in Australia.<ref name=\"MTVLiveAustClose\">{{cite web|title=Summer Channel Changes|url=http://www.foxtel.com.au/whats-on/summer-channel-changes/default.htm|publisher=Foxtel|accessdate=1 November 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140316184920/http://www.foxtel.com.au/whats-on/summer-channel-changes/default.htm|archivedate=16 March 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn March 2, 2014, MTV Live HD launched on [[Taiwan]][[CHT MOD]]. On October 24 that same year, it launched on [[UPC Romania]].\n\nStarting January 2015, after years of broadcasting as a free-to-air channel on [[Arabsat]] and [[Nilesat]], MTV Live HD became encrypted and available only on satellite TV provider [[OSN]] in the [[Arab World]]\n\nOn 15 February 2016, the standard-definition MTV Live closed and was replaced by [[MTV Music (UK and Ireland)|MTV Music +1]] in the United Kingdom. On 29 June 2016, MTV Live HD stopped airing on Sky in the UK, but continues on Virgin Media.\n\nOn 29 March 2017, it was launched in [[Portugal]] as an exclusive on [[Meo (telecommunication service)|Meo]].\n\nOn 3 August 2018, it was launched in [[Brazil]] as an exclusive on [[NET (telecommunications)|NET]].\n\nOn 1 January 2020, it was launched in [[Malaysia]], and [[Brunei]] as an exclusive on [[Astro (television)|Astro]].\n\n==Availability==\nThe channel is available in a number of countries throughout Europe, Latin America and Asia including:<ref>{{citation | title = MTV grows HD footprint | date = 14 July 2009 |accessdate = 1 November 2010 | publisher = C21 Media | url = http://www.c21media.net/news/detail.asp?area=1&article=50799}}</ref>\n\n*'''Europe'''\n**Albania, Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Croatia, Hungary, Czech Republic,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parabola.cz/zpravicky/13816/mtvn-hd-brzy-v-ceske-republice/ |title=MTVN HD brzy v \u010cesk\u00e9 republice! |language=Czech |publisher=Parabola.cz |date=2011-03-09 |accessdate=2013-07-12 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014172904/http://www.parabola.cz/zpravicky/13816/mtvn-hd-brzy-v-ceske-republice/ |archivedate=2013-10-14 }}</ref> Estonia,<ref name=\"c21media02\"/> Denmark, Finland, Germany, Greece, Israel, Italy, Latvia,<ref name=\"c21media02\">{{Citation | title = MTVNHD heads to Baltics | date = 1 February 2010 |accessdate = 1 November 2010 | publisher = C21 Media | url = http://www.c21media.net/news/detail.asp?area=1&article=53975}}</ref> Lithuania,<ref name=\"c21media02\"/> Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Russia, Serbia, Slovakia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Turkey, Ukraine and the United Kingdom.\n*'''Latin America'''\n**Argentina, Brazil, Chile, Colombia, Costa Rica, Dominican Republic, Ecuador, El Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, Mexico, Nicaragua, Panama, Paraguay,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.tigo.com.py/content/grilla-de-senales-cable|title=Grilla de Se\u00f1ales CABLE - Tigo Star|website=star.tigo.com.py|accessdate=4 May 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180328165219/https://star.tigo.com.py/content/grilla-de-senales-cable|archivedate=28 March 2018}}</ref> Peru, Uruguay, and Venezuela.\n*'''Asia'''\n**Indonesia, Malaysia, Maldives, Mongolia, Philippines, Singapore, Mainland China and Taiwan.\n*'''Middle East and North Africa'''\n**Lebanon, Syria, Iran, Iraq, Israel, Jordan, Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, UAE, Bahrain, Qatar, Oman, Yemen, Egypt, Libya, Tunisia, Algeria and Morocco.\n\n==Programming==\n===Current Program===\n* ... And Friends\n* ... vs ... vs ....\n* Diary of\n* High Definition Hits\n* Hot Right Now\n* Hot Spot\n* Leading Ladies / US Ladies\n* Making The Video\n* MTV Asks\n* MTV Crashes\n* MTV Essentials\n* MTV Live\n* MTV Rewind\n* MTV Unplugged\n* MTV World Stage\n* Powerplay! This Week's MTV Hotlist\n* T