537/http://www.artfacts.net/en/artist/perle-fine-97748/profile.html|archive-date=March 3, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://anitashapolskygallery.com/artists/fine-perle/|title=Anita Shapolsky Gallery, 152 East 65th Street, NYC {{!}} Fine, Perle|website=anitashapolskygallery.com|access-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304211001/http://anitashapolskygallery.com/artists/fine-perle/|archive-date=March 4, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*2017: \"Women in Abstract Expressionism\", Palm Springs Art Museum, [[Palm Springs, California]]\n*2019: \"Sparkling Amazons: Abstract Expressionist Women of the 9th St.\" The [[Katonah Museum of Art]], Westchester County, NY.<ref>http://artdaily.com/news/117349/Abstract-Expressionist-Women-of-the-9th-St--show-comes-to-the-Katonah-Museum-of-Art#.XZ9ZKCVlAc0</ref>.\n*2019: \"Postwar Women:alumnae of the [[Art Students League]] of New York 1945-1965\", Phyllis Harriman Gallery, Art Students League of NY; curated by Will Corwin.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/20/arts/design/new-york-galleries-what-to-see-right-now.html NY Times, ''New York Galleries: What to See Right Now'']</ref>\n*2020: \"9th Street Club\", Gazelli Art House, London; curated by Will Corwin.<ref>[https://www.dazeddigital.com/art-photography/article/47375/1/20-london-art-events-in-2020-to-leave-the-house-for Dazed Digital]</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Abstract expressionism]]\n*[[Action painting]]\n*[[New York School (art)|New York School]]\n*[[9th Street Art Exhibition]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==Books==\n{{further reading cleanup|date=November 2013}}\n*\n*Anderson, Janet A. [http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/23048676&referer=brief_results ''Women in the fine arts : a bibliography and illustration guide''] (Jefferson, N.C. : McFarland, 1991) {{ISBN|0-89950-541-4}}\n*Chiarmonte, Paula. [http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/20491155&referer=brief_results ''Women artists in the United States : a selective bibliograp